annotationA: Optic atrophy 1 (Opa1) is a dynamin-related GTPase that mediates fusion of the inner membrane of mitochondria. Opa1  usually works with Marf to coordinately fuse both mitochondrial membranes. Opa1 activity is regulated by proteolytic processing; Belongs to the TRAFAC class dynamin-like GTPase superfamily. Dynamin/Fzo/YdjA family
annotationB: Mitochondrial fission 1 protein; Involved in the fragmentation of the mitochondrial network and its perinuclear clustering. Functions downstream of Pink1 and upstream of Drp1 to regulate mitochondrial fission
